959
01:13:26,698 --> 01:13:28,491
Take my word for it.

960
01:13:30,035 --> 01:13:31,327
No.

961
01:13:31,703 --> 01:13:35,790
I know you feel bad.
You don't like doing his dirty work.

962
01:13:35,999 --> 01:13:39,586
-You know you're better than him.
-That's enough!

963
01:13:39,794 --> 01:13:43,965
But I'm not so sure.
Maybe you're worse.

964
01:14:44,442 --> 01:14:48,154
-lnteresting?
-Not very.

965
01:14:48,571 --> 01:14:51,741
You're used to reading
more high-toned stuff.

966
01:14:51,991 --> 01:14:53,993
Yes, I am.

967
01:14:54,411 --> 01:14:56,705
-What's the matter, kid?
-Nothing.

968
01:14:56,913 --> 01:15:00,041
-All of a sudden--
-I don't like that Jim.

969
01:15:00,250 --> 01:15:03,211
Why? What'd he do to you?

970
01:15:03,461 --> 01:15:07,298
He didn't do anything to me.
It's what he's done to himself.

971
01:15:07,507 --> 01:15:08,800
Done what?

972
01:15:09,009 --> 01:15:14,014
Paul said he could have been Assistant
Attorney General of the United States.

973
01:15:14,305 --> 01:15:17,017
-Who?
-Jim.

974
01:15:17,392 --> 01:15:22,397
-So what's wrong with that?
-So nothing's wrong. Look at him now.

975
01:15:22,605 --> 01:15:26,151
Hangs around. Helps you promote.

976
01:15:26,359 --> 01:15:30,697
Lets you walk all over him
just because you pay him.

977
01:15:31,281 --> 01:15:34,409
So we finally get around to me.

978
01:15:35,785 --> 01:15:41,583
I'm not sure I like you, either.
You're selfish, that's your trouble.

979
01:15:41,833 --> 01:15:45,295
-Since when is all this?
-Since now.

980
01:15:45,712 --> 01:15:51,176
I used to think you were a big man.
I'm beginning to see you're not.

981
01:15:51,426 --> 01:15:55,638
Through history there's been bigger
men than you. Now too.

982
01:15:55,847 --> 01:15:57,223
-Who?
-Thousands.

983
01:15:57,432 --> 01:15:59,267
Name one.

984
01:15:59,642 --> 01:16:01,353
My father.

985
01:16:02,187 --> 01:16:04,481
Twenty-five a week.

986
01:16:05,398 --> 01:16:08,693
Don't get nervous just because
you read a book.

987
01:16:08,902 --> 01:16:11,404
-You're as dumb as ever.
-Think so?

988
01:16:11,654 --> 01:16:16,034
Yeah, but I don't mind. You know why?
Because you're the greatest--

989
01:16:16,242 --> 01:16:18,328
-Leave me alone!
-Come here!

990
01:16:18,578 --> 01:16:22,082
-I feel like I wanna go away someplace!
-Where?

991
01:16:22,290 --> 01:16:24,918
-We'll go to Florida.
-I mean alone.

992
01:16:25,126 --> 01:16:27,796
-You've gone nuts! Calm down!
-I can't!

993
01:16:28,004 --> 01:16:29,673
-Why not?
-I don't know!

994
01:16:29,881 --> 01:16:32,884
I hate my life.
There's a better kind.

995
01:16:33,134 --> 01:16:38,306
lf you'd read some books you'd know.
Maybe you're right. I'm still dumb.

996
01:16:38,556 --> 01:16:43,311
But I know there's a better
kind of life than the one I got.

997
01:16:43,561 --> 01:16:45,563
Or you!

998
01:16:46,523 --> 01:16:49,567
You'd rather be with
that saxophone player?

999
01:16:49,776 --> 01:16:52,612
-At least he was honest!
-He was a chump.

1000
01:16:52,821 --> 01:16:56,157
-He worked for a living.
-I worked since I was 1 2.

1001
