-Nobody give me nothing.
-Robbing a house is work too.

1002
01:17:00,203 --> 01:17:02,455
In my whole life--!

1003
01:17:07,877 --> 01:17:10,213
I never robbed a house in my life!

1004
01:17:10,422 --> 01:17:13,758
-What are you talking about?
-You can't understand.

1005
01:17:13,967 --> 01:17:16,469
Get off that high horse,
you dumb pot!

1006
01:17:16,678 --> 01:17:17,929
You...

1007
01:17:18,138 --> 01:17:19,764
...menace!

1008
01:17:21,599 --> 01:17:24,811
You never had a decent meal
until you met me!

1009
01:17:25,020 --> 01:17:28,356
But I had to eat with you!
You got no manners.

1010
01:17:28,606 --> 01:17:32,652
Taking your shoes off all the time
and picking your teeth.

1011
01:17:32,861 --> 01:17:35,405
You're just not couth!

1012
01:17:42,328 --> 01:17:44,789
I'm as couth as you are!

1013
01:17:46,958 --> 01:17:50,503
-And that cheap perfume you put on.
-Cheap?

1014
01:17:50,712 --> 01:17:54,341
I don't own nothing cheap except you.

1015
01:17:54,841 --> 01:17:58,970
You don't own me. Nobody can
own anybody. The law says.

1016
01:17:59,179 --> 01:18:02,766
-lf I was scared, I wouldn't be here.
-Where are you?

1017
01:18:02,974 --> 01:18:06,269
You don't like it here, beat it!

1018
01:18:08,355 --> 01:18:11,524
-Wait a minute! First this.
-Not now.

1019
01:18:11,775 --> 01:18:12,984
-Right now!
-No!

1020
01:18:13,234 --> 01:18:16,696
I won't sign anything
till I know what it is.

1021
01:18:16,988 --> 01:18:19,407
Do what I'm telling you!

1022
01:18:21,159 --> 01:18:23,370
Harry, please don't!

1023
01:18:29,918 --> 01:18:31,503
There.

1024
01:18:45,767 --> 01:18:48,186
All right, now go on. Blow.

1025
01:18:48,937 --> 01:18:53,400
I don't want you bawling here.
You don't appreciate nothing.

1026
01:18:53,608 --> 01:18:59,239
Go sit on a park bench until you learn
how to behave. Go on, beat it!

1027
01:19:02,575 --> 01:19:04,661
This way out.

1028
01:19:05,161 --> 01:19:06,913
I gotta put something on.

1029
01:19:07,122 --> 01:19:10,917
Hurry up. I don't want you around.
You bother me!

1030
01:19:14,963 --> 01:19:17,799
Big fascist!

1031
01:19:41,114 --> 01:19:42,824
All set?

1032
01:19:43,658 --> 01:19:46,828
You think I'm gonna
let a broad talk back?

1033
01:19:47,078 --> 01:19:51,416
-Where is she?
-She's leaving. I can't stand a crier.

1034
01:19:51,666 --> 01:19:54,711
-What's she crying about?
-How do I know?

1035
01:19:55,879 --> 01:19:57,756
Becoming a strange girl.

1036
01:19:57,964 --> 01:20:01,634
She's all right. It's these books.
They got her nervous.

1037
01:20:01,885 --> 01:20:04,304
Educating her was a mistake.

1038
01:20:04,512 --> 01:20:09,517
I didn't know it would be like this.
I'll fire that Verrall skunk.

1039
01:20:09,726 --> 01:20:10,727
Why blame him?

1040
01:20:10,935 --> 01:20:16,858
He taught her too much. You know
what she called me? A ''fatch-ist'' !

1041
01:20:17,067 --> 01:20:21,821
That don't make sense. I was born
in New Jersey. She knows that.

1042
01:20:24,199 --> 01:20:26,409
What's the matter, Harry?

1043
01:20:30,330 --> 01:20:32,874
I love that broad.

1044
01:20:34,501 --> 01:20:39,547
You think we could find somebody
to make her dumb again?

1045
01:20:47,972 --> 01:20:51,434
Don't be late if you don't
want no bloody nose.

1046
01:20:54,020 --> 01:20:57,649
-Would you do me a favour, Harry?
-What?

1047
01:20:57,857 --> 01:21:00,402
Drop dead.

1048
01:21:54,164 --> 01:21:58,376
<i>I have swOrn upOn the altar Of GOd...</i>

1049
01:21:58,877 --> 01:22:01,421
<i>... eternal hOstility...</i>

1050
01:22:01,880 --> 01:22:05,258
<i>...against every fOrm Of tyranny...</i>

1051
01:22:06,343 --> 01:22:09,179
<i>... Over the mind Of man.</i>

1052
01:22:24,903 --> 01:22:27,405
Oh, hello. Chestnut-7 1 80.

1053
01:22:27,655 --> 01:22:31,534
I'd like to speak to
Thomas Jefferson, please.

1054
01:22:31,785 --> 01:22:35,288
Oh, no. I mean Thomas Verrall.

1055
01:22:36,623 --> 01:22:39,626
No, Paul Verrall. Paul Verrall.

1056
01:22:39,834 --> 01:22:42,379
Well, it's very important.

1057
01:22:43,713 --> 01:22:46,132
Well, I'll hold on.

1058
01:22:57,185 --> 01:22:59,104
-Jim!
-Yes?

1059
01:22:59,312 --> 01:23:01,106
-What time is it?
-1 1 :30.

1060
01:23:01,314 --> 01:23:04,192
-I'll slug her when she gets back.
-lf.

1061
01:23:04,401 --> 01:23:09,280
-She always winds up where I want her.
-I hope so.

1062
01:23:26,548 --> 01:23:27,465
Jim!

1063
01:23:27,716 --> 01:23:29,426
-What time is it?
-1 1 :30.

1064
01:23:29,634 --> 01:23:33,138
-You said that before.
-1 1 :31 .

1065
01:23:33,555 --> 01:23:38,476
-She's been gone eight hours.
-Maybe she's seeing a double feature.

1066
01:23:38,685 --> 01:23:41,604
That don't take eight hours.

1067
01:23:42,105 --> 01:23:44,774
-Could've had an accident.
-You'd hear.

1068
01:23:45,025 --> 01:23:48,319
Could have got attacked.
Happens all the time.

1069
01:23:48,570 --> 01:23:53,283
Not to Billie. Maybe the other
way around. But not to her.

1070
01:24:07,547 --> 01:24:08,798
She here?

1071
01:24:09,007 --> 01:24:11,426
What do you mean?
No. Look some more.

1072
01:24:11,634 --> 01:24:14,804
-I been all over town.
-Well, go over it again.

1073
01:24:15,013 --> 01:24:20,143
-Do what I'm telling you.
-Sure. Just changing my socks.

1074
01:24:22,145 --> 01:24:23,772
-Harry.
-What?

1075
01:24:24,022 --> 01:24:26,024
Marry her.

1076
01:24:27,150 --> 01:24:28,526
Still harping?

1077
01:24:28,735 --> 01:24:31,571
I'm thinking of your legal safety.
She--

1078
01:24:31,780 --> 01:24:33,698
I know what she owns.

1079
01:24:33,907 --> 01:24:36,201
You've got to do it, Harry.

1080
01:24:36,409 --> 01:24:41,456
Broads always hook you in the end.
All this because a dame reads a book.

1081
01:24:41,664 --> 01:24:45,168
It's the new world.
Force and reason changing places.

1082
01:24:45,377 --> 01:24:47,879
-What?
-Knowledge is power.

1083
01:24:48,088 --> 01:24:51,716
I don't like this. You stewed,
that broad out of line.

1084
01:24:51,966 --> 01:24:54,803
-And some congressman!
-I think he's cute.

1085
01:24:55,011 --> 01:24:56,721
I'd like to trade him in.

1086
01:24:56,930 --> 01:24:58,932
-On what?
-On a senator!

1087
01:24:59,140 --> 01:25:00,684
On a senator?

1088
01:25:00,934 --> 01:25:05,689
Take the blinders off and let in
the light. Just for a second.

1089
01:25:05,897 --> 01:25:10,902
You can't buy senators and congressmen
as if they wore price tags.

1090
01:25:11,152 --> 01:25:14,823
These guys are honest.
Sincerely trying to do a job.

1091
01:25:15,198 --> 01:25:19,160
Sometimes you find
a rotten apple, like Hedges.

1092
01:25:19,369 --> 01:25:23,373
But just once in a while.
In a great while.

1093
01:25:56,614 --> 01:26:00,869
Are you sure you're ringing
Mr. Brock's suite, operator?

1094
01:26:01,077 --> 01:26:03,747
Well, how about the bedroom?

1095
01:26:04,289 --> 01:26:07,125
Ring a few more times.
I wanna make sure.

1096
01:26:07,334 --> 01:26:10,462
-He's not in.
-Just one more ring.

1097
01:26:12,630 --> 01:26:14,007
Let's go.

1098
01:26:25,143 --> 01:26:27,854
The stuff's in his briefcase.

1099
01:26:28,063 --> 01:26:30,106
In his bedroom.

1100
01:26:32,650 --> 01:26:35,987
I probably won't see you again, Paul.

1101
01:26:36,196 --> 01:26:38,198
-I wanna say goodbye.
-What?

1102
01:26:38,406 --> 01:26:41,159
-And thanks.
-Where are you going?

1103
01:26:41,368 --> 01:26:45,121
-Away from here, that's all I know.
-Where?

1104
01:26:45,914 --> 01:26:47,665
You can tell me.

1105
01:26:47,874 --> 01:26:52,212
I don't know. I thought
I might go see my father for a while.

1106
01:26:52,462 --> 01:26:55,173
-I've got a better idea.
-What?

1107
01:26:55,382 --> 01:26:57,634
Let's get married.

1108
01:26:59,177 --> 01:27:02,013
You must be daffy.

1109
01:27:02,722 --> 01:27:05,016
I love you, Billie.

1110
01:27:06,768 --> 01:27:09,938
You don't love me.
You just love my brain.

1111
01:27:10,188 --> 01:27:11,815
That too.

1112
01:27:12,691 --> 01:27:17,821
I'll think it over, but I can
tell you now, the answer's no.

1113
01:27:23,785 --> 01:27:26,121
What are you doing?

1114
01:27:26,329 --> 01:27:29,666
lf you don't know,
I must be doing it wrong.

1115
01:27:44,222 --> 01:27:46,224
Fine time!

1116
01:27:50,687 --> 01:27:53,523
-Hello, Harry.
-Where you been?

1117
01:27:53,773 --> 01:27:57,610
I took a walk, like you told me.
I met Paul.

1118
01:27:57,819 --> 01:28:00,405
Okay, buster, knock off.

1119
01:28:02,866 --> 01:28:04,534
Good night, Paul.

1120
01:28:04,951 --> 01:28:08,079
Good night, Billie.
Good night, Harry.

1121
01:28:09,414 --> 01:28:13,001
What's the matter, Harry?
You miss me?

1122
01:28:29,392 --> 01:28:32,354
I got something to say
and I don't like to wait.

1123
01:28:32,562 --> 01:28:33,480
I know.

1124
01:28:33,688 --> 01:28:36,232
-Now I'm not so sure.
-Why not?

1125
01:28:36,441 --> 01:28:40,028
Talking fresh, slamming doors.
I knew you'd be back.

1126
01:28:40,278 --> 01:28:42,739
-You did?
-Jim was worried, not me.

1127
01:28:42,989 --> 01:28:44,783
Not yet.

1128
01:28:45,158 --> 01:28:48,411
-What took you so long?
-I had a lot to think.

1129
01:28:48,620 --> 01:28:51,289
-For instance?
-Where I stand around here.

1130
01:28:51,498 --> 01:28:53,416
-I'm trying to tell you.
-What?

1131
01:28:53,667 --> 01:28:54,959
Where you stand.

1132
01:28:55,168 --> 01:28:58,797
First, Verrall is out.
I don't like to see you upset.

1133
01:28:59,047 --> 01:29:01,257
-Next, we'll get married.
-No.

1134
01:29:01,466 --> 01:29:03,718
But you gotta behave--
No?

1135
01:29:03,927 --> 01:29:07,555
-What do you mean, '' no''?
-I don't wanna, that's what.

1136
01:29:07,764 --> 01:29:12,727
-In fact, I've never been so insulted!
-Who are you to say no?

1137
01:29:12,936 --> 01:29:17,357
Don't knock yourself out.
You got a lot of surprises coming.

1138
01:29:22,112 --> 01:29:23,738
-Just tell me.
-What?

1139
01:29:23,947 --> 01:29:27,492
-How can you not wanna marry me?
-For one, you're dumb.

1140
01:29:27,701 --> 01:29:32,789
I got a different kind of life in mind.
Sorry, you wouldn't fit in.

1141
01:29:33,039 --> 01:29:35,667
-I don't understand!
-I do.

1142
01:29:35,875 --> 01:29:37,544
What did I do?

1143
01:29:37,752 --> 01:29:42,590
I talked rough to you. Maybe I hit you
a couple of times. Easy.

1144
01:29:42,841 --> 01:29:45,719
Is that any reason
to treat me like this?

1145
01:29:46,011 --> 01:29:49,222
I done good too.
Can't we straighten it out?

1146
01:29:49,431 --> 01:29:51,099
-No.
-Why not?

1147
01:29:51,349 --> 01:29:57,022
All that stuff I've been studying,
it just mixed me up.

1148
01:29:57,230 --> 01:29:59,232
But when you hit me before...

1149
01:29:59,441 --> 01:30:04,320
...it was like it all knocked
together in my head and made sense.

1150
01:30:04,571 --> 01:30:06,364
I realized what it means.

1151
01:30:06,614 --> 01:30:11,786
How some people are always giving it,
and some taking. And it's not fair.

1152
01:30:12,037 --> 01:30:16,332
So I'm not gonna let you anymore.
Or anybody else.

1153
01:30:18,335 --> 01:30:21,963
Listen, kid. I got an idea.
You wanna come to Florida?

1154
01:30:24,049 --> 01:30:27,844
We used to have some good times
together. Remember?

1155
01:30:28,303 --> 01:30:31,181
I think you should
marry me. Don't you?

1156
01:30:31,389 --> 01:30:35,977
I want you to marry me.
Do what I tell you or you'll be sorry.

1157
01:30:36,227 --> 01:30:41,358
-I'm not scared of you anymore, Harry.
-You're not, huh?

1158
01:30:44,319 --> 01:30:47,155
-And something else. I'm leaving.
-What?

1159
01:30:47,364 --> 01:30:48,865
For good.

1160
01:30:49,240 --> 01:30:51,618
You just can't walk out.

1161
01:30:51,868 --> 01:30:56,164
You're in too deep. I was wrong
hooking you in, but you're in.

1162
01:30:56,373 --> 01:30:59,459
-I'm not gonna be.
-You wanna wash it up?

1163
01:30:59,668 --> 01:31:03,505
Fine! I'm too important
to monkey around with you.

1164
01:31:03,713 --> 01:31:06,591
Jim! Jim, wake up!

1165
01:31:09,386 --> 01:31:10,595
What is it?

1166
01:31:10,845 --> 01:31:15,809
-Come on, you've got some work to do.
-All right. Be right with you.

1167
01:31:16,059 --> 01:31:18,478
Okay. Well, get a move on!

1168
01:31:20,397 --> 01:31:23,900
I'll fix it so you're out.
You're spoiled. I spoiled you.

1169
01:31:24,109 --> 01:31:28,947
I was gonna make you be a real partner.
You don't want it? Fine!

1170
01:31:29,197 --> 01:31:33,576
And you don't look like you used to.
I'll be glad to be rid of you.

1171
01:31:33,785 --> 01:31:36,246
